headline: JPMorgan, Fifth Third Among Banks Facing Losses Tied to Tricolor
summary: Fifth Third said in a regulatory filing Tuesday that it faced an impairment charge of up to $200 million after discovering alleged fraudulent activity at a commercial borrower, which it didn’t identify.  The bank said it was working with law enforcement authorities.  Tricolor focuses on lending to borrowers across the US southwest who typically have poor or no credit scores.
